About 8 minutes after receiving vaccine, patient asked for water and reported that he did not feel well. He reported feeling faint and slight shortness of breath. The pharmacy staff gave him water and advised him that he could remove his mask to assist with breathing and began to observe him closely. The patient began to fee l better almost immediately, and was asked to remain in the observation area a little longer in case of worsening symptoms. During the next several minutes the patient experienced two more brief spells of faintness, which were relieved with more water and deep breathing. The patient reported that he had been working out in the sun earlier in the morning and that he was possibly a little dehydrated when he came in for his vaccine. He said that the symptoms he was experiencing were similar to episodes of dehydration he had experienced in the past. After about 40 minutes of total observation the patient said that he was feeling fine and that he felt fine to leave and drive home on his own. He walked around the store for a few minutes to make sure he would not feel faint while walking, and then left the building. I called and left a message for the patient tonight, and will attempt to call again tomorrow morning.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Moderna COVID?19 Vaccine EUA After getting the 2nd Moderna COVID shot, the patient was ok for about 10-11 days. Then, suddenly on March 25, he started showing high levels of dizziness and increasing blood pressure. We didn't think much of it and thought it was fatigue and asked him to rest. But, by April 2nd, his blod pressure was around 200/110. We rushed to ER. They conducted all the necessary tests and released him with his blood pressure holding around 170/100 asking him to go to a general practitioner. Then, on Monday we visited Dr. who recommended we wait for 2 weeks to see if the effects will dissipate to determine if it is neurological or if it is vaccine effect. It has been a very very slow dissipation of the side effects. He still has to walk very carefully and feels dizzy all the time. The impact has diminished about 20-25% in about 10 days but 6 weeks after his vaccine, he is still in trouble and is worried.
LAB_DATA: Chest X-Rays Brain CT Scan Urinalysis EKG POC Glucose Complete blood count Comprehensive Metabolic Panel Lipase Lactate Troponin CBC NT-Pro B-Type POC HGB In-person testing by Dr. HbA1C
OTHER_MEDS: Telmisartan  (40 mg) and Hydrochlorotiazide (12.5 mg) Gliclazide (60 mg) and Metformin (500 mg)
HISTORY: Good health. Walking around 2 hours a day, sleeping 7-8 hours a day, participating in daily activities without any issue for last 25-30 years.

On the day of my vaccine I had typical symptoms - chills, fatigue, and headache.  The next day I felt better, just tired.  On Tuesday the 23rd I returned to work and felt fine, but I did have an occasion of dizziness and I was tired.  I felt good on the 24th and returned to life/exercise as normal.  I woke up on the 25th in the early morning with a strange sensation in my head.  (I described it to my husband that it felt like I had worms in my head.)  When I got up I experienced dizziness that seemed like vertigo.  I tried to proceed with my day, but I got an intense headache, loss of appetite, and sore upper leg muscles.   I reached out to my doctors office.  I saw a doctor on the 26th.  (My dizziness was better, but I still had a headache and muscle aches.)  We discussed vertigo and possible reactions to the vaccine.  He also found some liquid in my ears and so we questioned allergies.  I got allergy medicine and took it when I got home.   The next day in the early morning the headache and muscle aches returned and I called a hotline through my doctor's office.  (The headache was quite intense.)  I spoke with a nurse - I was concerned that I may have Covid.  We discussed my reaching out to get a test if my symptoms were not better by Monday.  By Sunday I was feeling a bit better.  My headache had improved but I still had muscle aches in my legs.  I determined I would be able to go back to work on Monday.   The last symptom to remain was aches in my legs.  On Wednesday the aches were in my upper legs , by 3/30 the aches were in my ankles.  I was feeling better by early April.
OTHER_MEDS: Magnesium Citrate 250 mg D3 2000 IU Probiotic Supplement

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient noted on form that he had a severe reaction to peanuts which causes him to have anaphylaxis.  He stated that he does carry an EpiPen and any time anything with peanuts touches his mouth/lips he immediately notices his throat starting to close.  He also is allergic to cats.  Before administering the vaccine, the patient noted that he does not like needles and was not going to look.  I administered the vaccine and the patient and I exited the vaccination room.  I explained that he should sit in the waiting area for about 30 minutes due to his severe allergic reaction in the past.  By the time that I walked back into the pharmacy, the patient's wife shouted "He's not breathing!".  My technicians called 911 while I grabbed an EpiPen and rushed to the patient.  I immediately administered a 0.3 mg dose of epinephrine and observed that the patient had passed out, was not breathing, but had a pulse.  A few seconds later he regained consciousness and his breathing was erratic.  I gave him water and he stated that he felt very lightheaded and dizzy.  I instructed him to remain seated.  He also noted that his vision was blurry and he saw a black dot.  His wife was fanning him to cool him down while I tried to obtain the patient's blood pressure, but could not get a reading.  The paramedics came and evaluated him thoroughly.  His blood pressure, heart rate, EKG, and blood sugar were all within normal limits.  They determined that the syncope was most likely due to the patient not eating during the day and not liking needles.  The patient was feeling much better and declined further medical treatment, including going to the hospital.  He was instructed to go home and relax.
LAB_DATA: EKG, blood pressure, blood glucose, heart rate

I had my first Covid vaccine (Pfizer - Lot ER2613) on March 17.  No issues other than a soar arm the next day.  In fact, I went on a hard 7 mile run the next day as part of my normal training routine (currently training for a half Marathon.)  This past Thursday, April 8, at 6:00 pm EST, I had my 2nd shot (Lot EW0161).  For about the next 18 hours, I was fine other than the arm being a little sore in the morning. Late in the morning I noticed my back was getting very stiff and a bit sore when I moved around.  I have a desk job and spend a lot of time in front of the computer, but I normally stretch and move throughout most days, so I don?t have many back issues.  This was a bit worse than normal.  Usually, when I feel something like this, my go to remedy is an easy run.  I had a 5 mile easy run planned for that day, so later in the afternoon, after some dynamic stretching, I went for a run.  As I started, I felt some of the worse back pain I could remember and stopped running after about 50 yards.  I stretched a little more, questioning if I should continue, but decided that movement would be better than doing nothing.  I started running again and although the first mile was much more uncomfortable and painful than normal, I continued on for the 5 miles with everything eventually loosening up as the blood starting flowing.  I felt pretty good the rest of the day and into the evening.  In the middle of the night, I awoke numerous times with a bad ache in my back, which is very unusual for me. I tossed and turned all night from side to side, from front to back but could not stop the burn and pain in my lower back.  I took 2 Advil, but that did little to help.  I got out of bed about an hour earlier than normal and after a little light stretching, my back felt fine again.  I went for my weekly long 14 mile run an hour later and everything was good again and for the rest of the day.  The next 3 days / nights have been similar.  I continue waking each night with a burning and aching in my lower back and it continues all night long.  Once I stand up, get out of bed and start moving around, the pain and burning go away almost immediately.  I?ve never felt anything like this before.  I?m 57, male, am very healthy and fit (aiming for a 1:30 half marathon in 10 days.)  Never had issues with sleeping before this and haven?t experienced any back pain in a very long time.  I can?t think of anything I?ve done recently to trigger this other than the coincidence of the 2nd Pfizer vaccine shot.
OTHER_MEDS: Calcium Fish Oil One a Day vitamin (male over 50)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 7-10 days or so after receiving the first dose of the pfizer Covid vaccine I started to develop this red, nodule-like, painful "rash" on both of my forearms. Not only the left arm where the vaccine was administered. This did not go away after a couple of days, and I was instructed by a physician to being taking Benadryl. This appeared to alleviate the symptoms (no visible red nodules anymore)  4-5 days prior to my second dose, so I stopped the medication and presumed it was done. Then, within 4-5 hours of receiving my second Pfizer covid vaccine, I broke out into the same red, painful, nodule-like "rash" along both of my forearms. This time was worse than the previous reaction. I was instructed to take Allegra at the time by a physician, which I did for approximately 4 weeks. This seemed to get rid of the symptoms I was experiencing, and I could not visualize the nodules on my forearms anymore. However, after approximately 2 weeks, I noticed a painful and swollen vein in my right forearm, opposite arm to the one I received the vaccine in. I did not think much of it at the time, since I had no other associated symptoms. Then, over the next couple of weeks, it appeared to become more swollen and painful. Also, I saw another swollen vein near my knee. On April 6, I had labs drawn and CBC, CMP, TSH, and ESR came back normal, but the CRP was elevated. Thus, I was instructed to begin aspirin 325mg, which I took for 4 days beginning April 8th and ending April 12th. On April 13th, an official ultrasound confirmed a DVT in my right popliteal vein, a superficial thrombus in my proximal great saphenous vein, and a superficial thrombus in my right forearm where the pain originated from weeks prior. The initial presumption at this time is that the clots are vaccine-related, but could be linked to an underlying blood disorder that was triggered by the vaccine. Blood hyper coagulation labs have not yet come back. I was initiated on Eliquis starting April 12th for the DVT.
LAB_DATA: To date, on April 6th labs were ordered including a CBC, CMP, TSH w/ reflex, CRP, and ESR. All were normal, except CRP which was elevated. A complete hyper coagulability panel as well as other tests such as D-Dimer, ANA, and more were drawn on April 12th, but results have not come back as of yet.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got the J&J vaccine around 2:30pm on a Saturday and by 6 or 7pm I was experiencing a really bad headache. This headache extended down my back and around the back and top of my skull. Walking to even get water in the other room gave me motion sickness. I was shaking and sweating with a fever all night, was unable to sleep, and experienced hallucinations due to the high fever. The next morning I still had a fever but could finally sleep. I still had a bad headache, body aches, and nausea. I slept most of the day and my fever went down but was still >100 degrees all day. On Monday, I had a mild fever in the morning which went away by afternoon. I  felt weak all day Monday and still experienced body aches and a headache. By Tuesday, I was only experiencing fatigue and brain fog. This lasted about a week.
LAB_DATA: I did not go to the doctor.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: PMH of CAD, HTN, DM2, atrial fibrillation on Eliquis who was last seen normal at 2330. Family heard a thud in pt's bedroom and found him on the ground with left gaze. EMS called, placed pt on a C-collar and brought to ED as a stroke code activation. On presentation, pt with left gaze and right hemiparesis and LLE weakness. He was non-verbal and not following commands. Head CT showed no acute hemorrhage. CTA with perfusion did not show a large vessel occlusion or significant hypoperfusion. Clinical picture suspicious for ictal event so he admitted to the NSICU for further workup.
LAB_DATA: Etiology of symptoms remain most consistent w/ an ischemic infarct of the L MCA territory in the setting of known Afib. Repeat CTH on 1/22/21 showed subtle hypodensities in the L frontal/parietal region c/w subacute infarcts that explain patient's symptoms. During hospital course, patient continued to have dysphagia limiting ability to pass S/S evals. Eventually had PEG placed on 1/28. The was unfortunately c/b bleeding near PEG site, requiring multiple transfusions and reversal of eliquis w/ K-centra on 1/31. CTA abdomen/pelvis showed no evidence of intra-abdominal vascular injury or extravasation. Hgb subsequently remained stable between 1/31 and 2/3. Pt restarted on low dose apixiban 2.5 mg BID on 2/4, which pt has been tolerating well.    Of note, per family collateral, patient was actually taking apixiban 2.5 mg qday prior to his stroke, and thus, etiology now felt to be stroke 2/2 Afib on subtherapeutic anticoagulation.     Pt's AICD was interrogated on Jan 28 which showed only 1 event on Jan 15 (6 sec on NSVT to the 160s). Pt was never shocked; unlikely to be related to stroke event which occurred 1 week after this event.   On 2/7, patient was noted to have right field cut when he did not blink to threat on the right. Family reports no previous vision deficit. Repeat CT head was obtained which revealed no occipital stroke to attribute the vision deficit to. Ophthalmology consulted for decreased vision in R eye. No acute pathology found, visual acuity 20/800 in R eye, 2/200 in L eye    During hospitalization, patient was noted to have abnormal respirations and cough. Found to have bilateral pleural effusions and atelectasis. Breathing treatments and Lasix given. It was presumed that patient had developed an aspiration pneumonia. He completed a 5 day course of antibiotics on 2/1.    Patient was noted to be hypernatremic during hospitalization. Was started on free water flushes, which were increased accordingly. Water flushes were discontinued 2/6. Patient's sodium 144. Tube feeds were changed to bolus in anticipation of upcoming discharge.    Pt has no signs or sxs of TB   Admit NIHSS:  24
OTHER_MEDS: HOME MEDICATIONS:  Eliquis Metoprolol Levothyroxine Losartan Glipizide Pentoxifylline
HISTORY: PMH of CAD, HTN, DM2, atrial fibrillation on Eliquis

I was so cold my entire body was trembling.  I kept taking steaming hot showers but I couldn?t feel it, I was still freezing and shaking.  I was very weak and started having extremely horrible body aches and pains.  Specifically my legs were hurting the worst, I remember my hip joints felt like they?d buckle underneath me.  I got a headache that was unbearable.  It felt worse than a migraine.  It hurt to move my head or use my eyes at all.  I went to bed and was under several blankets and a heating pad while also running a space heater right next to me.  I still could not get warm at all.  I hallucinated that I could see each ache and pain on my body and watched them move through me.  By 4 am I was now hysterical and crying.  I was in so much unbearable pain and so scared.  I had to call off of work for this day.  I was so out of it I called my daughter off of school but also called for my mom to come get her and take her to school.  I kept my youngest home with me.  My head was still the absolute worst headache I have ever felt in my life.  I couldn?t open my eyes and it hurt to move at all.  I had to call a friend to come pick up my youngest daughter because I was unable to take care of her, I could barely stay awake and alert.  I tried another hot shower and everything still felt cold.  I was now nauseous from the head pain.  Around noon on this day I finally had the strength to drink some water and was able to take Tylenol.  I laid on the couch for hours still shivering and in unbearable pain.  I was still very scared that I was having such a bad reaction that I would die.  I called my husband to come home from work and be with me because I was scared.  I took more Tylenol a couple hours after the first dose.  Around 6 pm I started to feel better.  I was able to eat again that evening.  I had a headache though for about 3 weeks after that gradually weaned away.
HISTORY: Childhood asthma but haven?t had an issue with it in years.

39 y.o. female with history of asthma but no previous anaphylaxis to vaccines received covid-19 vaccine (Moderna) at 4:15pm today and within a few minutes developed tachycardia, nausea and vomiting  No shortness of breath, no wheezing, speaking in full sentences No chest pain  She has a history of asthma and hives to terbutaline, and anxiety reaction to gabepentin. No history of intubation or serious reaction from asthma  Transferred to the procedure room by RN with my assistance Blood pressure 132/82 pulse of 135, 02 sat 100% on RA, speaking full sentences, stating she had some chills lungs clear, tachycardic, and moving air well, no wheezing. Patient stated said she had to the bathroom right away, was going to have diarrhea.  Said she could walk, and was walked across hall with assistance to bathroom, where I stayed with patient.  I accompanied patient to bathroom, she had one episode of diarrhea, and dry heaving, returned to procedure room, lied supine, IV started, NS bag hung.  RN present, additional ARNP present, staff aware, anaphylaxis kit present.  Patient tachycardic and continued with normal 02 sat and good air movement, EMS with request for ALS activated due to reaction to vaccine.  I made decision to give epinephrine with her tachycardia and continued nausea with diagnosis of anaphylaxis, and as preparing epinephrine, patient stated she started to feel tight in chest, epinephrine given 0.3mg of 1:1000 IM. Lungs notable for reduced air movement lung bases. Patient denied throat tightening, rash, lip swelling, but she continued to have dry heaves, and stated she had a "sore throat". EMS had already been activated before first epinephrine dose. Awaiting medics, patient given Solumedrol 125mg IV, benadryl 50mg IV, and zofran 4mg IV Patient also given four puffs of albuterol MDI with spacer.  Medics arrived, patient still feeling tight in chest, blood pressure 125/70, 02 sat 100%, lungs still tight with reduced air movement  Patient given second dose of epinephrine 0.3mg, 1:1000 IM, approximately 7-8 min after the first dose. EMS transferred patient to gurney with transport to PEMC Patient alert during entire reaction.  PEMC notified.   To ED via ALS PEMC notified   Timeline of anaphylactic reaction: 1615: Covid Moderna 2nd injection given  RN notified of patient feeling rapid heart rate and nausea. Patient pulled back to procedure room.  1631: Vitals: BP 132/82, HR 135, Temp 97.1, O2 sat 100% 1637: IV start in LAC, NS running  1645: 0.3 mg IM Epi - administered by  RN  1648: 4 mg IV Zofran - administered by ARNP 1650: 4 puff Albuterol sulfate 90 mgc given via spacer - administered by  MD 1651: 50 mg IV Benadryl - administered by ARNP 1652: 125 mg IV Solumedrol -  administered by ARNP 1653: 0.3 mg IM Epi - administered by RN
LAB_DATA: no testing. Patient transferred to higher level of care - ER via 911 - ALS (EMS) transport.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I presented to the medical shot clinic event for my second COVID-19 injection on schedule. My injection was given by a nurse at the Hospital and while I did not watch the needle enter into my shoulder, I quickly developed the symptoms of adhesive capsulitis to my right shoulder within a few hours. Initially I did not realize why I was in such extreme pain but did notice that the injection site and bandage placed over top seemed very high. The next day I could not move my shoulder in any direction without severe pain. Regardless of this I still presented to work as I had no one to cover my shift but wasn't able to continue working due to the amount of pain and inability to use my right arm. My coworker is a family medicine Doctor who reached out to a local orthopedic surgeon and fortunately I was able to get a same day visit with the orthopedist. He diagnosed frozen shoulder on January 26, 2021 citing improper placement of the vaccine and I was prescribed a variety of medications including muscle relaxers and anti-inflammatory medicine. He offered to give me a shoulder joint injection however I was concerned about a corticosteroid affecting the efficacy of the Covid vaccine that I had just received. After only minimal relief with the medications that were prescribed hi was in directed by the orthopedic surgeon to start physical therapy which I did. Physical therapy sessions were only partially helpful, and I was still having limitations with my work duties as well as activities of daily living in my home (Such as being able to trust myself, wash my hair, use a blow dryer, doing light housework with my right arm well-being right hand dominant etc.). Finally, after eight weeks of conservative treatment not helping and daily pain I opted for a right shoulder joint corticosteroid injection at orthopedic office. Just a day after the steroid joint injection in my right shoulder I was significantly improved and for a few weeks I was actually pain-free. Unfortunately, a few days ago my shoulder pain started to recur and I have been advised by my orthopedic surgeon that the next step is an MRI and potentially more invasive treatments. I have no way of knowing the name of the nurse at the Hospital who administered my vaccine, and no reporting channels as I am not an employee of that facility. I was able to get the vaccine without being an employee because of my company's relationship with that facility. I have reported this to my employer however, as well as through the V-safe check ins.  I am discouraged and concerned that this may be happening to other patients going through that service for their vaccine.
LAB_DATA: I had three visits with my orthopedic surgeon between January 26, 2021 and March 22, 2021 as well as several physical therapy sessions with an outpatient physical therapy center and consultations with my primary care provider throughout this time. I had your shoulder x-ray during my first orthopedic visit on January 26, 2021. Because my symptoms have recurred, I will missing my orthopedic surgeon again for an upcoming consultation regarding the next step.
OTHER_MEDS: Nothing taken prior to the vaccine. Within the week prior, occasional use of OTC Zyrtec was taken for environmental allergy treatment

I received the shot at 14:30, in which medical staff in the jail's medical center watched me for 20 minutes to ensure there were no immediate reactions. I went about my day afterward with no symptoms. At 21:30 when I went to sleep, I got some aches in my joints and took 1 dose of liquid capsule NyQuil to help with the pain and went to sleep. At 00:30, the 7th, I woke up groaning in my sleep to the extreme pain in my joints and feeling hot internally. I decided to get up and take a warm bath to ease the aches. I went and ran the bath and all of a sudden while it was running, I had a severe need to throw up, but could not naturally. Since this was concerning, I got up and walked out of the bathroom and all of a sudden in the hall I got a feeling of impending doom and that something was not right and I fainted. I laid on the floor for what I would approximate to be 5 minutes going in and out of consciousness waiting for the blood to fully return to the brain. After this, I instantly felt like I needed to survive and that I felt like I could be dying so I slowly crawled down the stairs to get to my military ID so I could call the military's nurse advice line. I had to take a break and lay on the concrete in my garage because I felt so dizzy and so hot and began to feel my vision disappear like I was going to faint again. I waited a few minutes before getting back up the stairs crawling to my phone to call. When I called them 00:58, they told me to call 911 because they believed I would be having a severe reaction, though I noted to them I did not have a rash or hives. I then called 911 at 01:08. They sent EMT's to my home which took my vitals. I had normal blood pressure, SPo2, and temp, but an elevated heart rate of just under 100 and a high respiration rate. EMT's made the decision for me to stay home since the hospital did not seem immediate in their opinion. After this I stayed on the couch for a few minutes and then felt very tired so I walked slowly to my room and fell asleep. I woke up at 06:00 for work, and arrived at 07:00. In the hour after waking up I was achy, sweating, and felt light headed. I got to work and my Sergeant told me to go home and sleep. I slept another 5 hours at 08:00 and when I woke up most of my symptoms went away other than aches and getting flush very easily for 5 days.  At this current time all I notice is some random light headedness that quickly resolves and comes a few times a day at random and without cause.

Within 10 minutes of patient being observed, they noted they felt like they were going to pass out (lightheadedness, cold sweats). I asked patient if he would like to go back to the immunization room and lay down, he said yes. Walked him back with some assistance. Within 5 feet of the door, patient had trouble standing and said he couldn't see anything. I got the immunization room door open and patient lost consciousness. I helped him to the floor and elevated his legs. Within 30 seconds patient re-gained consciousness and was able to tell me if he was ok or not. He was able to converse, knew his name, etc. I told him I was going to go get an ice pack. I left the room for 60 seconds, got ice pack out of freezer, and alerted other pharmacist of the situation. Returned and patient was still lying down, conscious. Put ice pack near his carotid artery on neck. After 5 minutes, patient was able to get into seated position, unassisted. I stayed with him in immunization room for 30 minutes. He did not express any other symptoms other than being jittery and cold. He was able to walk around the room unassisted after 30 minutes. I asked if he had far to drive to go home or if there was anyone that would be able to pick him up. He said he felt ok to drive. I offered that he could stay under observation as long as he would like. He declined and was able to leave pharmacy on his own.

When I woke up on Sunday, April 11th, 2021 at around 9am, I have felt like my muscles have been ripped apart, I was sweating, I had labored breathing, and I could not get up for the day. I slept all day, feeling like I had the flu, and was sleeping until 7pm that day. I called out of work when I woke up because I knew on Monday I would not be able to make it, as I felt like I was very tired, lethargic, and sore. This feeling was throughout every inch of my body. I also went to take a shower that day and I had a hard time breathing in the shower, to the point where I had to sit on the edge of the tub, just to make sure I would not pass out from lack of oxygen. This was the scariest sickness I have ever had in my entire life. I literally thought I was going to die. Monday came around and I felt even worse, my muscles were sore, I felt extremely tired, I could not do anything, and I was in bed all day. Today is Tuesday, and I have felt a little bit better, but I have missed two days of work because of the effects this vaccine has had on my body. I made a virtual appointment with a doctor on the app on phone and met with Doctor who basically told me that the only thing I could do for myself is take Ibuprofen every 8 hours for the pain and swelling that might occur and drink plenty of gatorade. It is Tuesday, April 13th, 2021 at 11:29pm at night and I still feel the same as Monday, very weak, tired, and sore all over my body. I have never had this with a vaccine before, until I got the COVID-19 one. I have taken the Flu Vaccine, Hep A, Tantnius, Chicken Pox and never felt like I was so tired I could not get out of bed from these vaccines.
OTHER_MEDS: Effexor XR, Klonopin, Clonidine, Lisinopril, Metoprolol, Melatonin, Equate Men's Multivitamin, L-Theanine, Omeprozole XR.
ALLERGIES: Shellfish, SSRI antidepressants , Ativan, Opioid  painkillers, Buspar, antihistamines.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have many allergies and adverse events from prior vaccines, so I took a Benadryl before the injection. I was very pleased nothing detrimental happened at the time. My head and neck were a little itchy but went away, some dizzyness but went away, all after about an hour. The arm didn't blow up like usual.  That night, I started to experience the usual vaccine side effects i.e. headache, feverish, sweating, joint aches. All this I expected starting around 8:45 -9pm.   At about 10 - 10:30 pm, I began to have abdomen pain/pelvic pain... I started feeling like I was getting period cramps and lower intestinal discomfort. I just had my period though, so it didn't make sense (about 7 -10 days ago). I am also on the pill so I know for a fact I just had it and started a new pack. I was very confused and thought it was odd...can't be, maybe it would go away.   I woke up about 3am with intense uterus/period cramps which kept me up, in and out of sleep. About 5am I felt like I had my period (fluid down there), went to the bathroom and indeed, I was bleeding... a lot. The cramps continued, the bleeding continued and now 6 days later it is finally going away. I never get head aches and my head has continued to hurt on and off also.

Once my vaccine was administered I felt tingling on my tongue and bottom lip. I waited the 15 minutes and felt that the tingling was diminishing. I spoke to the tech and felt ok to leave since I was not experiencing loss of breath or swelling. After about 3 hours I noticed the tingling sensation coming back. I immediately called the pharmacist who administered the shot. After explaining the tingling was mostly felt on my lips and tongue but had no swelling and could breath and swallow just fine. I explained that it felt like when you get a shot for Dental work and that every time I touched the area it would tingle more. He told me that was not a normal reaction and would call in a few hours to check in on me. Sometime around 7 we spoke again and I still had no changes with the tingling. Again, he said he would have the pharmacist who was in call again the next day to make sure I was ok. By 11:30pm the aches in my joints started and I had chills. I woke up for work at 3:25am and noticed the tingling sensation wasn't as strong as the day before. Once I ate the tingling became more noticeable and was mostly on the right side of my tongue and throat. I also started experiencing a headache and sinus pressure. After arriving I work by 6am I felt exhausted. As the day went on the exhaustion  was becoming so strong I felt that I was fighting to keep my eyes open. The aches in my joints were becoming more intense especially in my hips and hands. At times I felt it hard to hold anything in my hand as closing my fingers became so painful it brought tears to my eyes. I also notice I was sweating profusely but had no fever. Once I was home I took a 2 hour nap. I woke up feeling the same the tingling in my mouth, aches still noticeable and headache still there. I could not stand and even tried to eat but had a loss of appetite. I called the pharmacy and reported the tingling was still noticeable. The pharmacist on duty explained the aches were normal but the tingling was not. I was advised to seek medical attention if I had trouble breathing or had swelling. The pharmacist told me to keep up on rest and fluids and I would recieve another call tomorrow to see how I was feeling. It's now 9:28pm and there are no changes to the tingling sensation in my mouth/throat. I still have aches and pains that are radiating throughout my body. My headache is still there but not as strong as this morning and I now have ringing in my ears. Every once in awhile I get some good stomach pains but they last a minute or two before going away.

Starting about 6 hours after administration I developed a headache and low grade fever around 100.1. I was ill that night and still feeling tired the following day and feverish. My left knee, which I had previously had a lateral meniscus transplant with a cadaver graft, starting swelling up and becoming increasingly uncomfortable. By Wednesday the 17th, I could barely put weight on the leg and the pain level had increased to 6/10, with 10 being the worst pain. This knee had previously been on a positive healing trajectory since my surgery. By Wednesday night, I couldnt put weight on it and pulled out the crutches to walk (I had been off of them since early February). I was dealing with a family emergency so did not have the capacity to deal with it at the time. Thursday morning, the 18th, all of my joints started becoming painful. I chalked this up to vaccine reaction. I was still fatigued and the knee was still extremely sensitive and couldn't bear weight. Friday and Friday night my joints became visible swollen and were so painful I was crying trying to find a comfortable sleeping position. I couldn't put any pressure on my shoulders for sleeping, the neck was stiff and tight, my hands and feet were visibly swollen with fluid and I couldnt even lift a cup due to the painful, enlarged finger joints. Every joint in my body seemed effected. Saturday morning I called my doctor who determined it was due to the vaccine and it seemed my immune system was attacking my joints. I was prescribed 40mg of predinsone in a 8 day taper. By 24 hours, the pain had receeded to a normal level of ache and I could put some pressure on my left leg again. By 48 hours after starting steroids, the swelling was reduced and I started to feel more normal. I have no history of autoimmune disorders or previous rhematoid issues.

elevated blood pressure, garbled speech, TIA Pt presented for acute stroke-like symptoms (L hemibody weakness, dysarthria, L gaze preference, dysarthria, word-finding difficulties) following a COVID vaccination (about 1-15 min after) at 1230 on 3/18/21. PMHx notable for multiple prior TIAa, HTN, HLD, PVD c/b R femoral artery thrombus (2017, no intervention, on Plavix), T2DM (prior A1c 6.5%, recently 6.2% not on meds), COPD, prior splenectomy (childhood re: car accident), chronic L ulnar neuropathy, bilateral hearing loss, complex partial seizure disorder following Rocky Mountain spotted fever. Symptoms resolved fully within 24 hours of event; diagnosed with TIA. MRI without new ischemic findings; chronic small vessel disease and chronic small R cerebellar stroke noted. TIA likely occurred in setting of hypertensive event with systolic BP to 220s. ED attending reported an NIHSS of 9. Of note, blood pressure was in the 210s systolic on admission, and subsequently down trended. Per resident, initially had left gaze deviation however on exam had full ocular motility. Pupils were of equal (size: OD 3, S 3) and reactive. Ocular motility was full without nystagmus. Facial sensation normal. Initial mild left facial droop, which also resolved. As the exam progressed, the patient's symptoms began resolving. Patient was able to articulate his thoughts better without dysarthria and strength markedly improved in the left upper and lower extremities to full 5/5 strength within about 30-45 minutes. NIHSS improved from 9-1. Of note, the patient reported having several episodes similar in nature, in the setting of significant hypertension as well. Denied ever having a true stroke in the past.
LAB_DATA: CT head was negative for hemorrhage or stroke. CTA head and neck was negative for any acute occlusion.

As a person with diabetes, I had to take extra finger sticks that day because I did not trust my normal sensation of low blood sugar. I think this is a common reaction to the vaccine, and I intend to get the 2nd dose, but maybe diabetics should be warned about confusing this common reaction with hypoglycemia and cautioned to be extra vigilant with finger sticks the day after receiving the injection.
LAB_DATA: Numerous blood glucose tests that day performed on my own glucometer, all were normal. Vaccine did not cause hypoglycemia, but it caused a feeling that I at first mistook for hypoglycemia. SYMPTOM_TEXT: This was one of the worst headaches I've ever had in my life. Migraine headaches run in my family so I'm no stranger to them, which is why it is particularly surprising. I was breathing heavily throughout, except for an hour or two of bad sleep. It was almost certainly a high fever, but I didn't measure. Chills, sweating. Complete misery. The extremely painful cycle lasted about 10 hours before it started to recede. I felt better close to 100% within 48 hours. I'm reporting this because I've realized that most people have "mild flu like symptoms" while my symptoms were extreme. If I had any other health issues (I don't) it seems obvious that it could have created a bigger problem. I didn't go to a hospital, but I should have, in hindsight.

On 4/8/2021 I developed a headache after receiving the Johnson and Johnson vaccine. I took the next few days easy, and laid in bed for the majority of the weekend. On 4/10/2021 I left my residence to get dinner and noticed I was short of breath just walking from the building to my car. The shortness of breath worsened over the next few days. On 4/13/2021 I called a clinic and told them I had been short of breath and they directed me to the ER. I arrived to the ER around 2:30 in the afternoon. They ordered a chest x-ray and ran a test to determine if I could have a blood clot. The test came back with results indicating I could have a blood clot, so they did a chest CT and an MRI. The chest CT showed a blood clot in my left pulmonary artery. They prescribed a blood thinner, told me to stop taking oral birth control, and discharged me.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The night of the vaccination (3/8), my body felt very hot (not fever) like it was going to catch on fire.  I took Tylenol to be safe and went to bed taking it as a sign that the vaccine was working.  I thought I was mostly over the next day, but four days later on 3/12, I started bleeding only two weeks after my last period, and the it was quite different than usual - very fresh blood and lots of it.  This continued for 15 days at time with very heavy flow - I bleed non-stop, and I worried that I was going to bleed to death.  The worst adverse effect happened 10 days after the vaccination on 3/18.  Out of blue without anything unusual, I started feeling very dizzy, nausea, and vomiting.  After much vomiting, nausea stopped, but the dizziness just got so bad, I couldn't move or even keep my eyes open (things were spinning even with my eyes closed).  I couldn't even stand up by myself.  This most horrible severe vertigo lasted two and got gradually better.  It took about 5 days before I felt safe enough to be alone by myself.  During this time, I had a excruciating headache on my left side.  It was so bad, I quickly took some painkillers which knock me out for a day.  The important thing is that I don't ever get headaches; this is the first one I had aside from one I had when going through IVF more than a decade ago.

thrombotic microangiopathy; This literature marketed report has been received from the authors of a published literature article, titled as stated below, and refers to a 5-month-old female patient who was treated with onasemnogene abeparvovec (ZOLGENSMA) for spinal muscular atrophy (SMA). On an unknown date, four days before onasemnogene abeparvovec (ZOLGENSMA) dosing, the patient was hospitalized for aspiration pneumonia. Her sputum culture grew Proteus and Acinetobacter species. On an unknown date, the patient received onasemnogene abeparvovec (ZOLGENSMA), one-time intravenous infusion administered concomitantly with corticosteroid (prednisolone 1 day prior to the infusion, and for a minimum of 30 days following treatment). On an unknown date, three days after onasemnogene abeparvovec (ZOLGENSMA) dosing, the patient developed second event of pneumonia. On an unknown date, six days after onasemnogene abeparvovec (ZOLGENSMA) dosing, the patient was vaccinated with a dose of haemophilus b conjugate vaccine (meningococcal protein conjugate) (manufacturer unknown) (exact dose, dose#, route of administration, lot# and expiration date were not reported), concomitantly with an unspecified influenza virus vaccine live (exact dose, dose#, route of administration, lot# and expiration date were not reported) and pneumococcal 4 6b 9v 14 18c 19f 23f conj vaccine (crm197) (PREVNAR) (exact dose, dose#, route of administration, lot# and expiration date were not reported), all for prophylaxis. On an unknown date, seven days after onasemnogene abeparvovec (ZOLGENSMA) dosing, the patient developed hypertension and decreased urine output as first symptoms of thrombotic microangiopathy (TMA). TMA developed with hemolytic anemia, hematuria, proteinuria, leukocytosis, thrombocytopenia, and severe hypertension. Renal ultrasound scan indicated diffuse increase in cortical echogenicity bilaterally. Functional TMA panel indicated evidence of complement pathway activation with no autoantibodies or abnormal complement components (low complement C4 (0.07 g/L), and normal complement C3 (1.1 g/L), complement Factor H (CFH) (369 mg/L), complement Factor I (34 mg/L), negative complement factor H autoantibody (CFHAb) (less than 50 AU), complement total (CH50) (160 U eq/mL), high soluble complex C3b-9 (0.9 mg/L)). Genetic evaluation was not performed. Other laboratory evidence of TMA included: hemoglobin 7 g/dL (Nadir) (on day 7 after onasemnogene abeparvovec (ZOLGENSMA) dosing; baseline: 10.3 g/dL); platelet count 17 k/micro-l (Nadir) (baseline: 503 k/micro-l); creatinine 0.7 mg/dL (peak) (baseline: 0.1 mg/dL); lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) 4208 U/L (peak). There was protein and blood present in the urine. Prothrombin time (PT), partial thromboplastin time (PTT) and international normalized ratio (INR) were normal. Stool and urine cultures were negative. ADAMTS13 (a disintegrin and metalloproteinase with a thrombospondin type 1 motif, member 13) assay was normal. The patient was treated with packed red blood cell (PRBC) and platelets transfusions, glucocorticoids, plasmapheresis, diuretic for fluid overload, antihypertensives. The features of TMA resolved within 2 weeks, except hypertension, which continued to persist 1 year later. The authors of the article considered TMA to be drug-induced by onasemnogene abeparvovec (ZOLGENSMA), resulting from immune-mediated etiology. Additionally, TMA was related to concurrent infection with encapsulated bacteria and vaccine exposure to haemophilus b conjugate vaccine (meningococcal protein conjugate) (manufacturer unknown), unspecified influenza virus vaccine live and pneumococcal 4 6b 9v 14 18c 19f 23f conj vaccine (crm197) (PREVNAR).  Upon internal review, TMA was considered medically significant.  A copy of the published article is attached as further documentation of patient's experience.
LAB_DATA: Test Name: stool culture; Test Result: Negative  ; Test Name: urine culture; Test Result: Negative

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Had history of delayed reactions to allergy shots in past and staff administering vaccinations were concerned about whether that might possibly occur with the COVID vaccination. Many of the delay had been 48 to 72 hours.  I didn't feel like going to the Farmer's Market and by 2 pm started getting a migraine headache which had be concerned.   I had not had any fever but had had arm pain that I had used a heating pad for.  I ate Saturday.  I started noticing neck stiffness and some difficulty moving my head right and left.  I had migraine headaches from age 13 - 50 with an increase during pregnancy so I knew what they were and  what I had started to experience as the night went on into Sunday was more than I had ever  experienced in my life.  Flat on my back, ice, no intake, tylenol/codeine, nothing did anything and and the intensity kept coming.  I vomited some Sunday evening which usually helps release the pressure, but nothing helped.  I continued to have more difficulty turning my neck from side to side, visual difficulties and excruciating pain.  I had a virtual appointment with my endocrinologist and she was concerned about what was going on and gave me some guidelines lines about managing my blood sugars and suggesting that I be on the Farxiga if I went in the hospital.  I made it through another virtual meeting basically holding my head in my hands.  I canceled all my dental and doctor appointments because of the unrelenting pain and my concern for my driving. I began having some spastic jerking of the head and neck, which with the mask on forced my teeth into my front gums and lacerated the wholes front inside of my mouth. On 3/23 my husband died unexpectedly, I canceled Wednesday's Funeral Home visit because of my concern regarding driving and the extreme degree of pain.  I could barely move my neck past center.  I was also having mobility issues and my right side was working as well as it should.  Typing and writing were difficult.  My pain level was off the chart.  I had spoken with the doctor and once I did the required things at the funeral home, I took myself to the emergency room.  My pain was coming off the right lower part of my neck, affecting my vision, my appetite, my balance--basically neurologically going downhill on a fast slide since Saturday night. I told the nurse that my pain level was 20+. The Spinal Tap in the ER was negative across the board and the fluid was clear.  IV's were hung to help with hydration.  Solumedrol and methacarbornol were given IV to deal with the inflammation around the vertebrae and the pain muscle spasms. Ice packs were applied to the front and pack of the neck to not only help with swelling, but with to relieve pain and help with neck alignment.  Blood sugars were a real struggle with all the prednisone on board but were helped some with the arrival of my Frixiga from home. It was the new Neurologist in the practice that looked at my posture, listened to my history and said, I am going to get some X-rays which took all day to do.  The X-rays showed that there had been swelling and shifting to make CI and C2 put pressure on the nerve. There was also a problem with L3.  A second neurologist added a morning dose of Topomax (50mg) which began to show some effect on Tuesday after being in the hospital for 5 days.  These 2 neurologist, along with the one in the ER could not rule out that what I experienced was a delayed reaction to the Moderna Vaccination, particularly as I have had delayed reactions to allergy shots in the past. It was suggested by the radiologist that a MRI be  one for a more definitive brain study as well as a spine study but the doctor on originally was doing much and didn't pick up on that. I have had to wean off of the prednisone at home which has meant wonderful monitoring of blood sugars. I have had to continue to wear the neck collar and slowly ween out of it.  I have been exhausted--the doctors think some of that may be from the muscle spasms and the fact that it took 4 days before there was a significant decrease in the intensity in the headache.  I still have to focus on posture and my right had gets very tired of the board.   Signatures are still not as  neat as they were but better than they were when I was admitted.
LAB_DATA: CT brain, CT spine, X-ray spine, lumbar puncture 3/25-26  Blood was drawn on admission
OTHER_MEDS: Breo Ellipta 200/25; Nasonex Nasal Spray 50mcg; Tessalon Pear. 100mg tid (as needed); Dexilant 60 mg 1 tab qam,; Ferrex 150 Forte 1 tab qam; Toviaz 8 mg 1 tab qam; Colace 100 mg2 tabs qam; Coricidin HBP (Cough & Cold) 1 tab  q 6 hr as neede
HISTORY: Type 2 Diabetes, GERD, Stroke (2016), 3 back surgeries, continuing back pain, irritable bowel, colostomy, kidney stone one kidney after left radical nephrectomy due to 10 by 13 cm benign tumor.  Gallbladder removed due infection of the gallbladder and not due to stones.  Balance issues resulted in fall and fracture of 5th metatarsal of right foot. Right IOL after removal cataract. History of severe bronchitis frequently requiring antibiotics. Asthma. Allergies. Osteoarthritis in right hand, right shoulder and right knee.  Problems with right rotator cuff. Mild migraines controlled by 100 mg Topomax at night.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin, Norgesic, Keflex, Novacaine, Talwin, Erythromycin  Adhesive Tape, Chocolate, Coffee, Cola, Cheese, Garlic, SEVERE Lactose intolerance, corn spices, tree grass, ragweed. air born pollutants; Cedar and all cedar-like plants, poison ivy, poison sumac. Animal dander. No Metformin due to severe abdominal pain and nausea and vomiting.  No flu shot until base changed--pneumonia X2 WITH 2 FLU shots

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Swelling of injection site, medium size nodules around vaccine site, left arm shooting pain 7 days post vaccine

I received the vaccine on March 24, on a Blue Day, when I was physically at work.  I stayed in the office until 5:00 pm and felt normal.  I could feel the place of the injection, but that was all.   The next day, March 25, I worked from home.  I woke up with a medium pain in the arm at the place of the injection and with a headache.  I said to myself, these are normal reactions following the vaccine.  The headache did not go away, although I took a Ibuprofen rapid tablet of 400 mg.  In the afternoon I checked my blood pressure and it was 171/90 and the pulse 86.  I took immediately additional blood pressure medicine (Captopril and Tertensif) to lower it.  In 2 hours it lowered it to 166/89 P81, at the advice of my physician, whom I called, I took the medicine I take for blood pressure Atacand and a pill to eliminate the water in the body.  Finally at 9:00 pm the blood pressure measured 149/81 P71.   On March 26 I came to work, with my blood pressure device, and at noon it was 198/94 P95.  I took two pills of Atacand and Furosemid and I came to the physician measured a blood pressure of 159/95, and subsequently 144/86.  She did an EKG which was normal.   On March 27, Saturday the blood pressure ranged between 132/74 P72 in the morning and 104/60 P 65 in the evening, taking only my usual medication for blood pressure.  And since then my blood pressure returned to normal taking only my usual treatment.      On March 29 I went to my cardiologist who examined me and did not find anything out of the ordinary, told me to continue with the same treatment, and monitor the blood pressure twice a day.  She of course, as anyone else, could not say it was due to the vaccine, but she could not dismiss the fact that maybe the vaccine had an influence over the blood pressure.  She encouraged me to take also the second dose of the vaccine.
2nd dose of vaccine very painful arm and large red , hot area  at injection site., beginning the evening of the shot.  Much worse than the original injection.  Painful swollen lymph node in same arm.
OTHER_MEDS: Losartan, Vit D3, protonics, Vit C,  Multi Vitamin.
PRIOR_VAX: Similar reaction to 1st dose

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient active-duty military on deployment at time of vaccination. Patient to return to later this week. Dr. and I remains on deployment and are best reached via e-mail or above phone number. 34 y/o active-duty male received the Jannsen COVID 19 vaccination on 29-Mar-2021. He describes expected symptoms of fatigue and body aches overnight, but reports development of melena the next morning, 30-Mar. On 31-Mar-2021, he developed nausea/vomiting and persistent diarrhea/ melena. He presented for care after an episode of syncope with extreme pallor and hypotension (BP 70s/40s). Hypotension and pallor resolved with 2L NS bolus and patient felt well and was dispositioned to quarters without further workup. On the night of 01-Apr, patient had a recurrent episode of syncope with recurrent hypotension. He was transferred to the ED and found to have a Hgb 5.0 secondary to GI bleeding due x3 peptic ulcers in different stages of healing. He received x4 units PRBCs and started on a proton-pump inhibitor. He continues omeprazole and iron supplementation. Hgb is now stable at 11.6. H. pylori pending. He will follow-up with GI physician. Of note, patient has had a voluntary weight loss of 30 pounds over the past x3 months. He has aggressive supplement use as above and reports exercising twice daily.
OTHER_MEDS: Insane Labz: Psychotic Diablo - 1 capsule per day, Insane Labz: Psychotic High Stim Preworkout - 1 scoop per day

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  The morning after getting the vaccine I woke up feeling very tired and sore/achey all over. I got to work (I lifeguard at the pool on campus) at around 6:15am and helped get the pool set up. When I sat down to try to do homework I started feeling very dizzy and nauseous. The pool deck is very hot, so I decided to try to go into the pool office where it would be cooler. I remember walking through the door and into the office, and then laying down next to the trash can because I thought I might be sick. One of my coworkers brought me some water and Goldfish, and I layed on the office floor for the rest of my 45 minute shift. Afterwards, when I was looking for my laptop, my other coworker said that when I had tried to go through the door into the pool office I had run into the door (I later got a small lump on my head from this) and that I had dropped my latptop. I do not remember either of these happening, so I believe that I blacked out for a moment, and it was likely hitting my head on the door that woke me up. A small scratch and some mild pain in my foot leads me to believe I dropped the laptop partially, but not completely, on my foot. I felt very tired for the rest of the day, and a little dizzy up until about mid-afternoon. I spent most of the day in bed sleeping. Waking up the next morning I felt completely fine, and was able to go about all of my normal activities with no side effects at all.
Error: Diluent Administered Instead of Vaccine

OVER THE COURSE OF 2 DAYS, THE PAIN BECAME WORSE. I CONTACTED MY DOCTOR AT FACILITY FOR A TELEPHONE INTERVIEW IN REGARDS TO WHAT I STATED ABOUT THE PAIN. CLOTS, SWOLLEN LYMP NODES ETC.. I WENT TO THE ER LATER THAT EVENING AND WAS TOLD THAT DOPPLERS WERE NOT COMPLETED AFTER 4 P.M. BLOOD WORK WAS PERFORMED BY HOSPITAL. MY LAB WORK WAS NORMAL AND I WAS ADVISED THAT I WOULD BE CONTACTED THE NEXT MORNING FOR AN APPOINTMENT FOR THE DOPPLER. ON 4/8@1:00 PM, I HAD THE DOPPLER PERFORMED AT HOSPITAL. I WAS TAKEN BACK TO THE ER AND WAS INFORMED THAT I HAVE DVT AND THIS WAS POSSIBLY LIFE THREATING. I HAD NO PRIOR HISTORY OF CLOTS. I'M CURRENTLY TAKING ELIQUIS FOR THE BLOOD CLOTS, WEARING A COMPRESSION GARMENT AND TYLENOL FOR PAIN. I WAS ADVISED TO HAVE ANOTHER DOPPLER COMPLETED IN 6 MONTHS

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient presented to the pharmacy to receive his Covid-19 vaccination. He was accompanied with his mother, who stated that she was there for support. It was not made clear to the vaccinator that the patient had a history of fainting with vaccines or blood draws. The vaccine was administered, and the patient immediately lost consciousness. The patient was placed in a chair with arms, and was caught before falling to the ground. The patient did not come in contact with the floor or any surfaces to cause further damage. The patient with quickly assessed by the pharmacist on duty and 911 was called by the other pharmacist. The patient quickly regained consciousness and was aware that he had "done it again". Neither the patient nor the mother were particularly concerned about the event, but we called the paramedics to be safe. The paramedics came and took vitals, everything checked out okay and the patient declined transport to the hospital. The patient's mother then drove the patient home.
HISTORY: Patient told us after that he has a history of fainting with injections.

My exclusively breast fed son started showing signs of atopic dermatitis on his right cheek and legs approximately 24-36 hours after I received my second COVID-19 vaccine. His skin got progressively worse over the next 4 - 5 weeks--both cheeks were affected, his neck, his trunk and back, and his arms. His legs were least affected. We saw the pediatrician on 4/9/2021 because his rash/skin reaction was bright red and "streaky" on his arms. His face also looked a little puffy to me under his left eye. Due to the timeline of the events and the fact that his reaction progressed over the course of a couple of weeks, it seems likely that this could be a reaction from my breastmilk that contains antibodies. There is some primary literature available that describes IgA and IgE levels in breast milk over time after COVID-19 vaccination. One such research letter was recently published online on April 12, 2021: SARS-CoV-2?Specific Antibodies in Breast Milk After COVID-19 Vaccination of Breastfeeding Women.
LAB_DATA: My son is currently on a 7-day course of oral steroids (prednisolone) and an antihistamine (loratadine). There is also discussion of obtaining some labs at his follow-up appointment in a few weeks: CRP, IgE, IgA, IgG, etc. His skin is greatly improved; however, I am concerned that it may worsen again after the steroid course is complete because I am still breastfeeding and plan to continue to do so. I have hundreds of ounces of breastmilk in a deep freeze as well that I would be glad to provide for testing.
OTHER_MEDS: PRENATAL VITAMINS, FISH OIL, VITAMIN D3, PROBIOTIC
HISTORY: BREASTFEEDING (2 MONTHS OLD AT TIME I RECEIVED SECOND VACCINE)

I had never experienced any kind of skin condition or reaction like that before. The Nurse Practitioner guessed that it was some kind of allergic contact dermatitis, with the inciting irritant unknown, and gave me a prescription for Prednisone to take over two weeks. By the time I got home the rash and itching had moved to my back, chest and stomach. The itching and rash subsided after I took the first couple doses of Prednisone that day. I finished out the prescribed dosage over the following two weeks. I have not had any more rash or skin irritation since March 28-29.

Within 1 minute of receiving the vaccine, I felt as if my body was on fire, along with dizziness and feeling like I was going to faint.  When I alerted the pharmacist, she brushed it off saying that I was just nervous. I waited the 10 minutes at the pharmacy and then left, still feeling dizzy and spacey. Then a feeling as if the vaccine was coursing through me, it was like an electrical shock feeling stinging me everywhere.  I called my mother being nervous, she ordered I go to Urgent Care. I told them what was going on, they wanted to call an ambulance. I said absolutely not since all of my vitals were normal. My breathing was normal. From 3-21 and on, I sporadically feel the electrical shock feeling at all different parts of my body. My skin also feels sunburned, but there is no rash anywhere. A day or two after, the left side of my face was swollen. That is currently no more. I went to my regular Dr., he strongly suggested for me not to take the second dose. He took blood to check for sediment rate I believe, that all came back normal. He referred me to an allergist, waiting to get that appointment.  To date, dizziness went away, sunburn feeling went away, electric shock feeling still comes and goes.  I never had any temperature, no tiredness, no rash.
LAB_DATA: 3-31-21 blood work at my regular doctor to check for sediment rate. That came back all in normal range. Waiting to schedule allergist appointment.
OTHER_MEDS: None I am 38 years old. The age field only accepted me being 37, I am not 37, I am 38.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After taking the Janssen single dose Covid vaccine I experienced headache, chills, low grade fever which went away by Saturday however I began a continuous low dry cough and GI upset/Diarrhea  that has lasted until today.

Around 5:00 PM after having gotten my shot, I arrived home from a drive down to meet my sister. Precautions were taken, masks were worn, safe social distance was maintained and I have no reason to believe any of the symptoms I experienced upon returning home were related to anything other than the vaccine, particularly since first that is how vaccines work and second one of my friends who was vaccinated at the same time as me at the clinic was going through similar pains.  It started as a discomfort in my intestines or possibly just below my stomach in general. I thought my pants were too tight but just in case I let my mom take over driving the rest of the way home. When I got to the house, I had about an hour of usable time left before I went into a complete state of delirium. We're not sure how high my fever actually got before my mom woke up and checked in on me at 9:00 PM, but after having pulled the covers away I registered at 102.5� F. I was screaming in a half-awake and half-asleep nightmare, trying to get someone to come help me and unable to get anyone's attention. I would, as a result, like to insist that it be added to recommendations to not be alone after getting the vaccine! For the whole first night! I believe that I genuinely could have died. My brain was melting for lack of more proper medical terminology, and I stopped being able to understand and speak my own first language in an incredibly confused state. This was entirely a result of two simultaneous factors: Fever and Chills. First, the fever made my skin ache. Wearing any clothing hurt. But once I took off my pants in exchange for some breezy shorts, I was covered in goosebumps and feeling frozen even though it was solidly in the 70s. I claimed under blankets and still couldn't get warm enough. The backs of my thighs were insanely hot in comparison to the fronts of them, so I just warmed my body under 3 layers of blankets trying to get the chills to go away. I did that for about four hours during which time I was basically constantly screaming incoherently.
HISTORY: Long term spinal issues likely due to weakness, spasms, and inflammation in back; asthma; "obesity" by the definition given for 1-C vaccination phase, though I would argue the validity of this particular measure.
ALLERGIES: Allergic to shellfish, crab, shrimp, chocolate, and others.

Nausea led to repeated vomiting overnight. I could not get out of bed to vomit, though I was able to lean over the side of the bed (bucket placed there) and eventually to sit up in bed to vomit. The joint aches began to subside but the nausea lasted for 24 hours. Walking I tripped/stumbled on four occasions the next day. (Am athletic; that was an anomaly.) Speech was affected; I used the wrong words  and found it challenging to find the correct one.  Short term memory is a little odd to date. The physical symptoms subsided within 48 hours.
LAB_DATA: I will visit a doctor next week.
HISTORY: Remission for many years: Crohns. Asymptomatic.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client passed out while seated in observation falling to the right side of the chair and onto the ground Client landed face down on the floor and was turned over onto his side first before being flipped onto his back  Client?s head did hit the ground Client reportedly appeared to be having a seizure when he was turned over Multiple people were present to assist client including nurse and EMT  At12:09, LVN called 911 and relayed information to the dispatch While on the phone, nurse went to get an Ambu-bag because staff present reported that the Client stopped breathing but had a pulse   Upon bringing the Ambu-bag, the Client had already regained normal  breathing pattern and no longer needed assistance breathing .   Ambu-bag was present but was not used Client was assisted into a wheelchair and taken to the private recovery area. Physician, nurse, and EMT were present  Client was alert enough to answer questions Client began to vomit / dry-heave for a short moment Client asked EMT about transport billing and was informed that he might possibly get a bill  but that he had the option to choose not to pay it  At 12:20, Vitals taken BP 155/112, Pulse 64  Client informed of the need to be further evaluated at the hospital Client verbalized multiple times that he did not want to be transported even after speaking with the physician  Physician suspected that the client had some underlining reason that he did not want to disclose regarding his refusal to be transported At 12:25,  Vitals taken BP 135/83, Pulse 58, O Sat 97% Blood sugar reading 104 Client reports no pain in the head, no nausea Client reports that he did not eat anything prior to coming At 12:31, Ambulance arrives  EMT briefs paramedic regarding the incident and the client?s history Paramedics questioned client  Client signed  form and verbalized that he did not want to be transported and felt well enough to leave Client called his brother to drive him home At 12:41 Client was wheeled in the wheelchair to the car Client informed of selfcare and instructed to go to the hospital / ER if symptoms worsen or headaches develop Client informed to let further vaccine administrators know that he passed out in the past and needs to have the injection lying down Client verbalized understanding Client?s brother drove him home
OTHER_MEDS: Client reports that he recently took a blood thinner pill for inflammation of the gums

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Lethargy, impaired cognitive function began on 3/29.  By the morning of 3/30, the lethargy and cognitive function is back to normal. My resting HR is about 70, but my HR was at 125 - 130 and I was not exerting myself and was sitting. My HR remained high after I went to bed, and chest pain became worse. By 12:30 am on 3/31, chest pain was getting severe and had pain in both arms. Went to ER at around 3 am on 3/31. Later learning I had a mild heart attack. I once again have perfect blood pressure readings and perfect HR.  I have returned to normal daily activities as of 4/4.
LAB_DATA: EKG, ECG, Blood work, and heart catheterization. Blood work revealed elevated enzymes indicating damage to the heart. All other tests were normal

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Lost his vaccine card would not give him a new one.  He got his vaccine, had burning sensation immediately after the needle was pulled out.  About 5-10 minutes later he started sweating, and seemed to have calmed down and felt OK.  He was observed for 30 minutes there and went for observation for another 30  minutes.  He went to another doctors office and at about 15:00 started feeling light headed and weak.  He drove back home, picked up some stuff at a grocery store, and outside the grocery store in 80 degree heat he felt the need to put on a jacket as he had the chills.  he went home, went to bed feeling bad, his shoulder was still burning where he got hte vaccin.e  He had a little bit of site pain, applied topical and the pain went away.  He woke up the next morning feeling really bad, felt like a major flu, his head felt like it was going to explode, but no problem with sinuses, no cough, no sneezing.  His eyes were watering from the pain, and chills on and off.  He had to change his sheets a couple of times due to sweating.  He then developed a fever of 99 degrees at about 18:00 that night, and about 19:00 he went to 102 when he checked it.  After that it went to 103, and about 15 minutes after that it was 104, and then higher at 104.+.  He took some vodka, honey and lemon juice and took an alcohol bath and the fever had not broken yet.  He called the clinic and they told him to call 9-1- 1 and to go to the ER.  He went to the ER at about 10:00, gave him fluids, did a chest x-ray and released him about midnight.  He apparently disoriented and tried to walk off and didn't remember this.  They took him back to the gate and called his son.  He went home, took another bath and woke up in sweat and was in bed for the entire weekend.  He got up Monday morning, 4/13/21 feeling a little bit better and went to see his doctor, who does not believe he was having any side effects and that the information that is being reported is true.   He is still feeling a little weak and still fatigued and on bedrest.  He was taking Advil besides his regular medicines every 6 hours with 500 mg of Tylenol for the intense pain as every joint in his body ached, and the worst headache he had ever had, as well as the high fevers.  His fever subsided on Saturday morning, and still had some sweats following that.  Did have hot/cold flashes on Saturday and Sunday.   He was given a COVID test in the ER and he was negative, but did not give him any other information regarding his lab work.
LAB_DATA: Lab work in the ER.     He had a chest x-ray and was told that it was negative.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Inflammation of a sebaceous cyst that had never been inflamed before (I've had it for several years) after both doses of the vaccine.  (First dose is the date stated in the form filled out, second dose was exactly 4 weeks after the first dose.)  The cyst is close enough to the vaccine site that it was included in the localized inflammatory reaction I experienced after both doses.  It became inflamed shortly after the first dose, and became increasingly inflamed (after seeming to stay the same or die down in the intervening 4 weeks) within 48 hours of the second dose.   Inflammation was above and beyond what surrounding "normal" tissue experienced, and lasted longer.  Initial response after first dose was occasional "weeping" of clear fluid (not pus) and occasional slight tenderness.  Response after second dose has been a continuation of the occasional clear fluid, plus slight additional swelling and moderate to severe pain that has subsided to moderate to mild pain since 48-72 hour mark.  Does not seem to be infected, but is still inflamed after vaccine response. I already have an appointment to have it excised next month, and am not overly concerned about this, but thought the reaction was enough to merit reporting in case others are experiencing similar prolonged inflammation for similar or other dermatological conditions near injection sites.

If I did anything (shower or carry a simple laundry basket) my arms would hurt so bad, I was out of breath and my heart was pounding so hard.  By the week of March 29th - I was laying down in the middle of the day, no energy at all.  Called the doctor and because of the shortness of breath & Body aches, they would only schedule a video visit for Monday, April 5th.  After talking to me, they schedule to see me that day at 11:45 AM.  I had weak muscle response in my arms, pale, and out of breath.  They did blood work.  Two hours after getting home; they called and said I needed to get to the emergency room.  My red blood cell count was dangerously low, and they ordered a blood transfusion.  I sent 6 days in the hospital.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Day 1 - Received 1st dose of vaccine at 4pm. Felt fine until 11pm when arm started to hurt, but not too bad. Had trouble sleeping. Day 2 - Woke up and entire arm hurt so bad, I could barely touch it and even the fabric from my loose shirt hurt my arm when the fabric put pressure on my arm. Had a large lump where the vaccine was administered in my arm. Was very tired all day and arm hurt. By 5 pm, I had a fever, my entire body ached, I had a sore throat and I was freezing and incredibly tired. Had trouble sleeping all night again.  Day 3 - Arm still in severe pain, woke up nauseous, and was very tired.  Had trouble sleeping again. Day 4 - Arm still hurt a ton, but less severe than previous days, very tired and slightly nauseous. Day 5 - Arm still hurt and tired.  Day 6 - Arm still sore, not as bad, still tired and worn out. Lump finally getting smaller on arm.  Day 7-  Arm still sore, but less than previous days. Tired still. Day 8 - Arm slightly sore. still tired.  Day 9 - (March 31st) Woke up and had bright red rash on arm where vaccine was given and rash was spreading across arm very quickly - it hurt and itched. Also developed a rash all over my entire face. Called Primary doctor and directed to take Benadryl and Motrin every 6 hours and go to the ER if it got worse.  Day 10 - Rash on arm and face persisted for 3 days, but kept under control by taking Benadryl.  Day 11 through Day 24 - rash still on arm but less severe/ red - skin where the rash is peels off and on (like when you get a sunburn). Mostly gone on day 24, but you can still see where the rash was on my arm when you look.    Note: Never had COVID so it's unclear why I had so many reactions to the 1st shot compared to other people.
LAB_DATA: None. Just kept in contact with my Primary Care Doctor.
HISTORY: IBS, Colitis, Gallbladder removed October 1, 2020, possible auto-immune disease
ALLERGIES: food sensitivities, nothing serious cannot take gabapentin (medication)

I had varicose veins in this leg for years, but this was different.  It was painful, swollen, red, warm and the vein is hard.  I was scared a DVT may be developing and went to the ER.  An ultrasound showed there was no DVT and was told to take ibuprofen for the pain and heat to the leg and a diagnosis of  Thrombophlebitis.  I followed up with a vein doctor. He preformed an extensive ultrasound, showing a watch spot for a possible clot turning into a DVT and placed me on blood thinners for 6 weeks, and to wear compression hose.   I know I had previous varicose vein problem in this leg and the vaccination did not cause this, but I do think it caused the Thrombophlebitis.  I am reporting this because this should be looked into, there are others with vein issues that maybe should be aware of this possible side effect.,

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Low grade fever (100.7), chills, body aches, headache, fatigue, mild nausea, hypersensitivity to sound, and a deep sense of doom/sadness/despair, which could have been severe fatigue.  I took Tylenol which didn't help. I called CVS and spoke to the pharmacist who said to also take an NSAID, which I did several times over a few days.  These clinical signs mostly resolved w/in 24 hours, except the fatigue and headache.  I was exhausted and slept a lot during the following week.   I also began to have chest flutters, flashes of dizziness and flashes of doom/despair in the middle of concentrating on something completely different, like at work.  I listened to my heart with a stethoscope after the flutter event was over and there was no arrhythmia at that time of auscultation and my HR was 74-80.   Each of these happened a few times the next week. Now those are mostly gone.   I continue to be tired and fatigue easily and need to take 1-2 hr naps in the middle of the day or after work, when I can.    Yesterday at work (4/13/21) I had extra sensitivity reaction to a repeated high pitched noise which, though didn't seem like would cause a lasting issue, then did cause me to be very fatigued and agitated afterward.  I also did then have an earache which hasn't resolved.  I am not sure if related to my original sound sensitivity. SYMPTOM_TEXT: 2nd maderna vaccine was given to my dad on 02/26/2021 and on 03/15/2021 my dad was visiting me all day and he acted fine and normal. At the end of our visit between 8 & 9 pm we went to the store where he started to gasp for breath. He had to keep stopping and said he couldn't breath. I had him sit several times because I didn't know how bad it was. By the time we reached the doors to leave after a short trip  he almost fell over and he became confused and said he couldn't breath. I had another customer get my dad a wheel chair close by while I called 911. The ambulance came quickly but at the hospital my dad went into cardiac arrest and his heart stopped 2 or 3 times and it had to be restarted. When I was able to get to the hospital my dad was on a ventilator and sedated. They had put him on medicine to blast the blood clots they had found. They said he had 2 very large blood clots with one on each lung. Later his kidneys started failing him and they said he would need to go on dialysis as soon as the next day. Later that night they told me my dads heart was shutting down and he had developed pneumonia. My dad died that night and I had to watch him take his last breath. If you want further information please contact Medical center would be the ones to contact for all information and my dad was in the critical care unit.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I ran a few errands after the vaccinaction and got home about 3:30pm.  All of a sudden I began to feel hot and dizzy.  Then the muscle aches started so I went to bed.  But this time it didn't go away!  Today is now 4/14/2021 and I am still having muscle ache in my right upper thigh and right side buttocks.  It is lessening but it also keeps me from getting a good night's sleep.  I've never had such a sensation.  Even after my hip replacement surgeries I didn't have this kind of discomfort.  I sure hope it ends pretty soon. For the past 2-3 years I have a routine of walking a minimum of 2 miles daily and that's during the winter as well since I'm up here in my state.  I'm strong and I'll get over this but I never expected this.  It feels like a "virus" has settled into the muscle tissue surrounding my right side hip implant.  I keep walking and doing my other exercises but it's very tiring.  Just wanted someone to know about this.  And, no, I did not bother going to the doc's with this.  Why would I?  The 'brainwashing' of the past 30 years about not bothering to go to the doc's if you have a cold because it's a virus and there's nothing we can give you for a virus has really worked.  I stay away from the doc's as much as possible!
OTHER_MEDS: Same as just reported....I thought I could report the effects of both doses on the same form....
HISTORY: Same as just reported but note that both hips were replaced in 2016.

Pt. was very sick the day after the shot, then Friday morning his heart was going into atrial fibrillation and jumping between 110 heart rate and 160+. He was out golfing when he noticed this. He rested later that day but was extremely tired and felt sick. Saturday morning (2.5 days after vaccine) he needed to go to the emergency room because his heart rate was back over 160. The EKG showed sinus tachycardia and gave him a message for it but it made it worse and the rate was over 200. They had to stop and start his heart then put on beta blocker which brought it to 180, then another beta blocker brought to 150. Following EKGs showed atrial fibrillation, postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome, and super ventricular tachycardia. Pt. had this about a year ago but was fine after a few days. This was the first time he was hospitalized for it and is now on daily medications. He fears the Moderna vaccine triggered it and is very worried about the second dose.
LAB_DATA: EKG, urine tests, ultrasound and others
