ER evaluation confirmed CT finding of right superficial vein thrombosis just above the sternoclavicular joint - see imaging report info.
LAB_DATA: CT ANGIOGRAM HEAD AND NECK IMPRESSION: 1.Negative for dural venous sinus thrombosis. Bilateral filling defects seen in the transverse sinuses are most likely arachnoid granulations. 2.Negative for DVT in the internal jugular or subclavian veins in the neck. 3.Filling defect seen within a tortuous superficial vein adjacent to the right sternoclavicular joint, consistent with a superficial venous thrombosis. The exact origin of the vein is uncertain but it appears to drain into the right subclavian vein via some engorged collaterals. Surrounding mild soft tissue inflammation and venous varices are noted. This corresponds to the site of patient's symptoms and palpable abnormality. The right subclavian vein itself is free of clot at this time. 4.Approximately 2.2 cm diameter likely extra-axial hyperdense lesion in the anterior cranial fossa extending to the right of midline, without any adjacent vessels in the area to suspect aneurysm. This most likely reflects a planum sphenoidale meningioma. Recommend follow-up evaluation with nonemergent contrast enhanced MRI. She was not feeling necessarily bad at that time but did start noticed that she was having some pounding headaches and felt like her heart was pounding out of her chest. Patient was concerned about her blood pressure running so high, and she is a physician so she did prescribe herself some atenolol. I received my shot at 10 a.m. on a Thursday morning. Around 6 p.m. on the evening of the shot, I began experiencing severe chills, and I threw up once. The chills lasted approximately four hours. In addition, I had an extreme headache. Once the chills subsided, I began sweating profusely through my clothes. I still had the headache. Around 2 a.m. in the morning, I was unable to stand or speak for about an hour.  Once I was finally able to move again, my skin - not my body, but my skin - hurt all over. I could not lay on my back due to extreme pain in my skin, particularly the skin on my back, shoulders and buttocks. Anything that touched my skin, no matter how light of a touch, felt like I was being severely bruised. My skin was in pain for about four hours. The sweating continued through the following Sunday morning.  I soaked through multiple sets of clothing and woke up every morning completely drenched. When I weighed myself Sunday morning, concerned about dehydration, the scale reflected a 4.2 pound weight loss over the course of less than three full days.  The headache lasted through Tuesday, April 14th, a total of five days with a strong headache. I am still experiencing some sweating but not like the initial round of sweating. Because my shot was given on a Thursday, I only missed one full day of work. However, had the shot been given at the beginning of the week, I am confident that I would have missed at least three full days, it was so debilitating.
LAB_DATA: I've not had any medical tests or lab work done. I treated the symptoms with iburofen and Gatorade.
OTHER_MEDS: No medication, dietary supplements or herbal remedies were taken the day of the vaccine.
HISTORY: I was anemic in the past, but to the best of my knowledge, I have not been anemic in the most recent/last couple of years at the least. I have struggled with extremely heavy menstrual cycles, as well.
ALLERGIES: In the past, I have experienced allergies to penicillin in the form of a rash only.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Delayed urticaria - extensive

(Saturday)When I came home after I received the vaccine I didn't really have anything to do, so I decided to take a nap and rest. I think after I woke up is when I started to feel the side effects. I can't remember exactly but I started feeling cold. I didn't think too much of it I just thought it was a cold day (which was quickly turning to night). Later that night I started feelinga bit dizzy and my head was hot but I still had chills. Since I had a had a blanket with me, and I think I was starting to feel what would become muscle aches, I just didn't want to move from the couch to my room. Feeling chills the rest of the night, I realized it was bad choice, since one of my family members left a window open. The cold air of the night really exacerbated my chills. Despite the cold I was still able to sleep, but the next day (Sunday) I did have a slight cough which I think was from experiencing the cold air of the night and not a side effect from the vaccine. (Sunday) This is when I really felt all the side effects. I felt weak, chills, headache, dizziness, muscle aches,(I'm not sure if I had a fever, I couldn't think clearly my head felt hot). I haven't had a hangover but I think that is what it would feel like to have one. I basically slept most of day Sunday ; This time in my room with  3 blankets (light blankets )and heat up (felt like 80�F under blankets). I was sweating under the blankets but it really helped warm me up and alleviate my chills. I woke up later that day to a call to help my sister with some work. I couldn't drive, felt weak and dehydrated(dark orange/yellow pee), but she insisted so she picked me up and scolded me for not eating anything all day(besides the side effects I mention, I think I may have also lost my appetite because I felt dizzy). I was still feeling my head aching after I woke up, still had muscle aches and a slight cough too. It was raining that day so I put on a winter coat with layers underneath to help with my chills. At her home she gave me a Gatorade (and water) which I think really helped since I was sweating a lot under the blankets when I fell asleep. She also gave me some home cooked meals she made. The combination of drinks, food, and familial concern really helped me recover. By Monday my cough was gone and the side effects had worn off to the point that I could go to work safely.   My mother & father also received vaccine at the same time I got it. My father also experienced side effects but his started later with the most effects felt on Tuesday. My mother did not get any side effects.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the first Pfizer vaccine on 3/16/21 in the afternoon. I am a young, healthy woman with no pre-existing health conditions: I don't smoke, am under 120 lbs., no allergies, etc. Two days after the vaccine, I started to experience an eye twitch, which progressed into Bells Palsy by the following week: by 3/23/2021.   I went to an urgent care clinic and was diagnosed as such, and they contributed to the vaccine and told me not to get the second shot. They also advised I get a CT scan to rule out a stroke, which I did,  on 3/24/21. I expect that they also reported this. I have facial paralysis on the left side of my face, and developed an ear infection a week after this...I don't have allergy issues, and have not had an ear infection since I was a small child. This has been traumatic, uncomfortable and very scary because I thought I was having a stroke.
LAB_DATA: CT scan ruled out a stroke. Urgent Care doctor diagnosed me with Bells Palsy and contributed it to the vaccine. I have the paperwork.   So far, my face has partially but not completely recovered....my left eye and left side of mouth do not function as they did prior to the shot. I feel fatigued, and my ear is getting better, but not totally recovered.

She says I need to see ENT.  Prescribes a ?migraine cocktail? ? magnesium, 2 benadryl and Zofran.   3-22-21(mon) 3:30pm  ENT, hearing test.  No changes since December of 2019 (went in for ringing in ears).  Talked mostly with physician assistant,  identified that I most likely needed the Epley maneuver on the right side.  Audiologist, was not available that day (I was supposed to have appt with her, but they made a change).  The earliest she had an opening was 3-24-21.  Dr. recommended taking magnesium  for head. 3-24-21(wed) 10:30 am  appt.  She performed the Epley on the right side one time.  Said that she wanted my body to calm down.  Keep head up for rest of day, sleep on two pillows.  Don?t lean over with head down.  Next day to walk around and use full range of motion on head so my brain/eyes get back to normal.  Scheduled a follow up for afternoon 3-26-21(48 hours) to assess progress.  She recommends to take ?preventa migraine? vitamin.  Magnesium and riboflavin (I start taking 3/28/21).  Able to roll over in bed without room spinning. 3-31-21(wed) 11:00 am.  She runs the test where I am in a dark room and she spins my chair around, watching what my eyes do.  Apparently I passed that test?  Then she tests me to check the inner ear crystals.  I am not in need of the Epley.  But, I feel terrible.  She says, something else is going on.  We have gotten the crystals back in place, she has done what she can for me.   1:00 pm appt with Dr.  Says chronic migraine.  Recommends vestibular therapy. 4-2-21 (fri) 3:00pm appt with PT, DPT, ATC, MS.  She identifies that my eyes are not tracking properly, the left one.  ?VOR deficit?  She says don?t google it b/c I have a mild case.    Homework is brain exercises:  pencil pushups and seated gaze stabilization with head rotation.  We schedule 2 sessions per week for 4 weeks.  She is hopeful of full recovery with work.  Says I would not recover by sitting in a dark room.  We need to retrain the brain and get back to normal.   4-7-21(wed) 10:00am appt for vestibular therapy.  Work on brain exercises, she times me.  Add some neck exercises to strengthen those muscles.  I notice a ?pinching? sensation on left side.  When I laid down on the foam roller, I had to put hands down to stabilize myself (room spinning).  2:00pm appt with deep tissue massage therapist.  (I have been working with her for over a year)  my head is very tender.  My neck and shoulders are extremely tight.  I have a large knot at the base of my skull on the left side.  It took a long time for my body to calm down today. 4-8-21 (th) 2:30pm appt.  Not feeling great  - suspect that I have ear crystals out of position again.  She sees me and says let?s test you.  She performs several Epley maneuvers.  3 on right side and one on left side.  Left me dizzy, unsteady and lightheaded.  I need help walking to car after appt.  go home and crawl in bed.  Cold, exhausted.  Slept for hour or so. 4-9-21(fri) don?t feel great.  Still waiting on body to calm down after Epleys. 4-10-21 (sat) still feeling yucky 4-11-21 (sun) Rolling over in bed, room spinning (left side).  when I sat up in the morning, my body swayed.  Was very dizzy walking to bathroom.  Headache.  Pressure in head/ears.  Those symptoms subsided slightly as the day wore on.  Sleeping Sunday night was better.  Rolling over was fine. 4-12-21(mon) headache,  pressure, ringing in ears.  Working on computer is fatiguing.  Head feels full/ fluid.  Rolling side to side / feel fluid move? / increases dizziness.
